messages.text: Alright, just let us know if anything changes!
But they gave me some meds for the pain and they don’t zonk me out or anything, so I ought to be good for Thursday.

I mean, as long as I don’t have to really move around much, I’m all right to just post up and present my poster as people come around. But yeah, like a tall chair is perfect. It’s basically when I go from like a deep sit to standing or vice versa that it kinda sucks, hah.
Dude, take care of yourself first! You can present to the instructors privately. But if you are doing better then I'm sure we could find a chair for you...

Just went and got a CT scan. I’ll find out later tonight, but I think I probably slipped a disc or something. Will it be possible to have a stool or tall chair or something by my poster so I can prop myself up for Thursday?
If something comes up I let you know. I think it's just the presenters practicing.  Do t forget about your readme/resume/talent profile...
I likely won’t be in today because of my back/seeing the doctor again. I have phone notifications on for Slack, though, if there are any issues with my submission or there’s anything I need to do.
I have your comments...come get 'em if you're here.
Yeah, I'll be good for tomorrow. I'm assuming I'm in reasonable enough shape unless the notes are crazy. Today was just a tough turnaround since I didn't prioritize the rough draft.
Thanks bud, hope you feel better...I am planning on writing notes on the print out for you. Don't forget 10am tomorrow! Otherwise Frank might flip out on you!
If you need to track me down at all today, I’ll either be around here the whole day or run to the doctor in the next hour or so. Haven’t quite decided yet.
